[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating static final in Native Image**\n\nI'm considering whether Native Image supports unsafe writes to static final fields. It seems like constant folding might occur, where the native image build could treat the field as potentially null. If it sees the final field, it may fold it, which means if we reach and write to it at runtime, it might not execute the Field#set. That could lead to failures, which makes it tricky. I'm wondering if we could catch that case somehow, but I can't skip the native aspect.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0bc0152183978deb0169f956412a6c81978a47f9b74b0e7105\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-VZSk29UoGaeQlgpjZN_bIbigvzhamS25y7YpKS2rMV236L1MZxpQAZBf2z2b8B0YcId8lk-efro5-mRDw1TOGnQfLN0h1oIS9c-He7huC2bL03Zv3Vc-jptNO2No7OdAfQLx4Bdqtxdz9iPjnrOV0FAonUvMosj5TsyAtSBfwe2gQmKrVM-Ejz0P4GBdxuiGLsh1AYkOGERVa66XYFH6fvE5HnRQ2P0oWdPLq31TTZox1jlBqOsVmBfXGJLRScbnxoW9kdXlgylfBo9fcYi3YymcfQ__kXkUvkeBeHlqb6K7tHnvnxW6a_W_b4FLjIuQvehm_1jIJKIwl1YMq0BC6VIKEgPIl8A4xbrIvE-AlHOc5JWmblEax_CetUyf6sEiZbBS6zIYx0OIiVcviP9Hq_v1qMbUZofCokVnKKRmMZbkDGHEz6IuKsYXTYdZXQKUllCyJgv7kkKfeGg4YIS8393K8JR4_tUH_BgEm6fWyFw_SB9VNE3nsgCMiNDpO7-t1MJS7LlD3DmQg0CkWA6-Uv4GB8x1O_RMhV9qmp7T2En_aAa00K_R1bBrsRDhsb4JeVYcKdzHIN-EnskzdIaulIpSeYTgJMG9YSp-tGZAYUM6kQyAtxAgnA-WEwaxsemw04ncAEUwv-vlJEmJWR--iW0Dr-3pk_wYgVhHAskPiJ-zZYgdL0xIRVXD5TKGVJvGE9pibm9dlJD-JRL2OUVeARTc9wp_JpeBQAHGT10JnEK-LOkl-uAoPqH3qqVL8okAvU9KdwmYWwqOIYZVkbq4d-lAJC2JZ3LG0H3eypoRUcrCwBC0cqXH4ADkwghwqStVOu0LLXM5F8MJX_Y_JkeJeu-RIoBtskkxmfGk1cZXHn51HglM0O5C9wfxsAN7af1RR22KuKcaagko25Fgj8Paey2A7o9_zDVaWj_ZAMOBSw-X-I7GPGLo-ckQYxD9-Er3JQEJZzlreDyxF0wdZ5Z8E_uhntbxJWhmBYuLRFSnmSwDaVPiWbvOPRVRVlp-bkIMl7qGv45JBwQMC_9bmNqFkZ8pvwojby2kp9Px9iK-hgHdYHD0PRqEgMLrg2HAISqKur5Rv4pF6O3AGGZ_53NLoGVnCCrD3tlr-bpi859jWLF9PQA4tMiXowdwd3As2qLTh-YSHZhSiJCTfbQnM9abBeEneStVeeKc6cX3tRoHEZJreB-QIbPT4rUPQvj97TchG4lvBJlB0rkTx